</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,466,1732]" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,275,1626,1652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">Notes.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Legalov &amp; Liu" authorityName="Legalov &amp; Liu" box="[652,1134,1626,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Attelabidae" genus="Euscelophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mayongi">
<emphasis box="[652,927,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">Euscelophilus mayongi</emphasis>
(Legalov &amp; Liu)
</taxonomicName>
in its coppery coloration and the absence of a protuberance on the pronotum, but it can be distinguished by its larger size, very dense vestitute and flat, not depressed frons.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
